title: Coronavirus: First case of virus in New Zealand
first-para: The first case of coronavirus has been confirmed in New Zealand. Authorities are now scrambling to track down people who may have come into contact with the patient.

title: Covid 19 coronavirus: US deaths double in two days, Trump says quarantine not necessary
first-para: US President Trump tweeted on Saturday night (US time) that he has asked the Centres for Disease Control and Prevention to issue a "strong Travel Advisory" but that a quarantine on the New York region" will not be necessary.

title: Coronavirus: Jacinda Ardern urges calm as panicked shoppers empty supermarket shelves
first-para: Panicked shoppers have forced the closure of a major food wholesaler on Saturday and today despite the Prime Minister urging New Zealanders to go about their daily lives after the country's first case of coronavirus.

title: Coronavirus: Rest homes and retirement villages plead for national aged care response plan
first-para: The aged care sector is urgently asking health authorities to coordinate a national response to the coronavirus threat.

title: Australia's first coronavirus fatality as man dies in Perth
first-para: Australia has recorded its first coronavirus fatality as a man confirmed as Covid-19 positive has died in a Perth hospital.

title: Coronavirus: Death confirmed as six more test positive in NSW
first-para: A 95-year-old woman has become the second person to die from the coronavirus in Australia, with six more cases confirmed in New South Wales on Wednesday.

title: Second US coronavirus cruise tests negative amid delays and cancellations
first-para: It was revealed a second cruise ship was being tested for Covid-19 in California at the same time as quarantine measures were put in place on the Grand Princess cruise ship.

title: Coronavirus: Russell Brand cancels sold-out show in Australia
first-para: UK comic Russell Brand has cancelled a sold-out Australian show over coronavirus contamination fears.

title: Coachella officially postponed: Coronavirus delays festival until October
first-para: It's official - one of the most popular music festivals in the world,Coachella,has been postponed until October.

title: Coronavirus: What's the difference between a pandemic,an epidemic and an outbreak?
first-para: The coronavirus is on everyone's minds. As an epidemiologist,I find it interesting to hear people using technical terms – like quarantine or super spreader or reproductive number – that my colleagues and I use in our work every day.

title: Coronavirus: Jacinda Ardern expects further 'tough' travel restrictions in NZ
first-para: New Zealand has had some of the toughest border restrictions in the world to stop the spread of coronavirus - and it plans to move further very shortly,Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern says.

title: Coronavirus: NZ First's Tracey Martin was with infected Australian MP Peter Dutton a week ago
first-para: NZ First's Tracey Martin is in self-isolation and will be tested for coronavirus today after a meeting with Australian Government Minister,Peter Dutton,who has tested positive for the disease.

title: Coronavirus: Canadian prime minister Justin Trudeau's wife tests positive for virus
first-para: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau's wife has tested positive for the new coronavirus,his office announced Thursday night.

title: Coronavirus: People are sharing their playlists on Spotify to help get through the pandemic quarantine
first-para: Music fans and coronavirus victims have taken to Twitter to share their 'pandemic playlists' via Spotify.

title: Coronavirus: Portugal gives nationwide standing ovation to healthcare professionals
first-para: What started as an idea on social media has turned into a daily nationwide tribute to the healthcare professionals working tirelessly to help a nation fighting coronavirus.

title: Coronavirus: Most overseas arrivals still not getting health checks
first-para: Most overseas arrivals at Auckland Airport were still walking into New Zealand with no health checks on Sunday,despite new rules which Prime Minister Jacinda Ardern described as "the toughest border restrictions of any country in the world".

title: Coronavirus: Kiwi traveller stunned at lack of health checks at New Zealand airports
first-para: A Kiwi traveller was left stunned after claiming Auckland Airport hadn't run any health checks on passengers arriving back from Hong Kong this morning.

title: Coronavirus travel restrictions: Self-isolation deadline pushed back to give airlines breathing room
first-para: The self-isolation deadline has been pushed back to give airlines a bit of breathing room.
